official_title: A bill to protect a segment of the Genesee River in New York.

summary.text: Genesee River Protection Act of 1989 - Applies the protections afforded for rivers listed for study for potential addition to the National Wild and Scenic Rivers System to a specified segment of the Genesee River in New York. Declares that such protections shall not interfere with the Secretary of the Army's management of Mt. Morris Dam.
